      "body" : "Er, hey.  It's not desirable to have the blockchain on the airgapped walletÃ¢ÂÂ god forbid someone figure out how to trigger a bug in its blockchain parsing.   ... More importantly your airgapped wallet might be a dumb smart card.\r\n\r\nInstead the normal client should maintain your balances, create the transaction... but when it goes to sign it it will find out it doesn't have the private key.   So it creates a signing request, which you shuttle over to the secure wallet (somehow). The secure wallet asks you to approve the transactionsÃ¢ÂÂ showing you the outputs and values (perhaps supporting batches), then signs them all, and you shuttle them back over to the main client for injection into the network.\r\n\r\nAlsoÃ¢ÂÂ I described how to solve the running out of addresses problem here: http://forum.bitcoin.org/index.php?topic=19137.0  (the type-2 proposal)\r\n",
      "created_at" : "2011-06-28T16:13:16Z",
